ZH: 反射是光线在物体表面的倒转现象。
EN: Reflection is the phenomenon of light being reversed on the surface of an object.

ZH: 镜子能够反射光线。
EN: Mirrors can reflect light.

ZH: 如果你站在玻璃窗前，你会看到自己的反射。
EN: If you stand in front of a glass window, you will see your own reflection.

ZH: 反射是声波在物体表面的反弹。
EN: Reflection is the bouncing back of sound waves on the surface of an object.

ZH: 反射板可以帮助纠正摄影中的光线问题。
EN: A reflector can help correct lighting issues in photography.

ZH: 这个墙壁的表面非常光滑，光线会产生完美的反射。
EN: The surface of this wall is very smooth; light will produce a perfect reflection.

ZH: 学生在镜子前面尝试了反射实验。
EN: The students tried a reflection experiment in front of the mirror.

ZH: 鱼在水中时，它们的形象会通过水的反射而扭曲。
EN: When fish are in the water, their images become distorted through the reflection of water.

ZH: 在太阳光的反射下，湖面闪烁着金色的光芒。
EN: Under the reflection of the sunlight, the lake surface glistens with golden light.

ZH: 那个玻璃窗上有很多指纹，光线的反射受到了影响。
EN: The glass window is covered with fingerprints, affecting the reflection of light.

ZH: 反射是光线根据物体的角度改变方向。
EN: Reflection is the change in direction of light based on the angle of an object.

ZH: 水面的反射使得船只的影像变得有些模糊。
EN: The reflection on the water surface makes the image of the boat somewhat blurry.

ZH: 探照灯的反射使得演唱会的舞台更加闪亮。
EN: The reflection of the spotlight makes the stage of the concert brighter.

ZH: 反射可以用来测量声波的速度。
EN: Reflection can be used to measure the speed of sound waves.

ZH: 每个镜子都有不同的反射效果。
EN: Each mirror has a different reflection effect.

ZH: 光线经过多次反射后形成了一个虹。
EN: Light forms a rainbow after multiple reflections.

ZH: 骑车时，要时刻注意车后镜的反射。
EN: When riding a bike, always pay attention to the reflection in the rearview mirror.

ZH: 在音乐厅里，音乐的声音在墙壁上进行了多次反射。
EN: In the concert hall, the sound of music undergoes multiple reflections on the walls.

ZH: 科学家利用激光的反射来研究微小的物体。
EN: Scientists use the reflection of laser to study tiny objects.

ZH: 镜子里的反射允许我们看到自己的外貌。
EN: The reflection in the mirror allows us to see our own appearance.
